data.content:
Three things break. Here's each one with the fix:

---

**1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — no longer takes an expression tree**

The parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`. Your expression-tree building code won't compile. Replace it with simple imperative code:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

**2. Complex type column names — two changes**

**(a)** Duplicate property names across complex types (e.g., `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) are now **auto-uniquified** (appending a number) instead of silently sharing a column. To keep explicit control:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});
```

**(b)** Nested complex types now use the **full path** in column names. `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of the old `BillingAddress_City`. To preserve old names:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

⚠️ Both changes affect existing database schemas — either add a migration or pin column names with `HasColumnName`.

---

**3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter**

All methods (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter containing potentially-redacted SQL for logging:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual executed SQL
    }
}
```
